[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    21[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The code calls `table.scan()` and only processes `response.get("Items", [])`. DynamoDB Scan returns at most 1MB of data per call. If the abbreviation table exceeds 1MB (unlikely for hundreds of items, but possible if the table grows or has large attributes), the response will include a `LastEvaluatedKey` and the remaining items will be silently dropped.
